# CODING DISCIPLINE

## Behavior
- One task at a time. Do not refactor while adding features.
- Do not change files outside the current task scope.
- Never change the Mission schema without confirming first.
- Never change Redis stream names without confirming first.
- Read the existing file fully before editing it.
- Match existing code style — do not introduce new patterns without asking.

## Python rules
- Use SQLModel for all database models.
- Use async FastAPI patterns.
- Use aioredis for Redis operations.
- Do NOT add --reload to uvicorn (breaks pyttsx3 TTS cache).
- All config from environment variables or .env files.

## React rules  
- Tailwind CSS only for styling.
- State via React hooks (useState, useReducer).
- NO localStorage or sessionStorage (not supported in this env).
- Fetch from control plane (port 8001) for all data.
- Use SSE endpoint for real-time mission updates.

## Commit rules
- Stage only files changed in this task.
- Commit message format: `feat(scope): what changed`
- Do not commit .env files.
- Verify diff before committing.